Libmatrix: an ANSI C-library which implements full and sparse matrices
 as structures of pointer arrays

Copyright (C) 27-03-2014 Frank Everdij
Delft University of Technology
email: F.P.X.Everdij@tudelft.nl

Based on the matrix block idea by Ted Jensen's feb 2002 post:
 "A Tutorial on Pointers and Arrays in C"
see: http://home.netcom.com/~tjensen/ptr/cpoint.htm

